cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DM, cs.NE 

This paper involves the problem of discriminative subgraph selection for graph classification, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The application domain is neurological disorder identification, which falls under the category of neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also involves the use of multiple side views to improve the classification performance, which is related to the field of multi-view learning (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the use of a branch-and-bound algorithm for efficient subgraph selection, which is related to the field of combinatorial optimization (cs.DM).
